brands.description: In computing, kill is a command that is used in several popular operating systems to send signals to running processes in order to request the termination of the process. In Unix and Unix-like operating systems, kill is a command used to send a signal to a process. By default, the message sent is the termination signal, which requests that the process exit.

transcript.text: Welcome to this tutorial on the Auto Translation feature in your admin panel.
This feature allows you to translate your entire Front Store website into the selected language with just a single click, providing A seamless browsing experience for your global customers.
To use this feature, navigate to the Languages section in your admin panel.
Here you'll find a list of all the activated languages for your website.
Next to each activated language, you'll notice a special auto translation icon.
Simply click on this icon for the language you wish to translate your website into.
The system will automatically translate all front Store content, including text, menus, labels, and other visible elements into the chosen language.
As soon as the translation process starts.
A message will appear with the status and a link to see the log.
Once the translation process is complete, your website will instantly display the content in the selected language, ensuring a smooth and user friendly experience for visitors from around the world.
Additionally, you will find the auto translation icon for all the applicable pages in the admin panel.
For example, on the product description page, if you want to translate the descriptions into Spanish language, you can simply click on the auto translate icon against it and the process will start.
Once it is done, you can verify that the content has been translated into the selected language with the auto translation feature.
Breaking language barriers has never been simpler.
Start using it today to enhance your websites accessibility and connect with a wider audience with just a single click.
Thank you for watching and we look forward to seeing how these updates help enhance your business operations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
